The paper focuses on safe and efficient crowd navigation for mobile robots, which is a core problem in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method utilizes a graph representation and deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper incorporates human gaze data to learn attention mechanisms, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
